```

## Shared Components

Place in `shared/components/` only when used across 2+ features:
- `StepCard/` — universal step display
- `WarningBadge/` — warning display
- `QuickActionBar/` — quick action buttons
- `CoachMessage/` — coach-style message bubble

Feature-specific components stay inside `features/*/ui/`.

## Forbidden UI Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ useEffect for data derivation → use useMemo
useEffect(() => {
  setComputedValue(expensiveCalc(data));
}, [data]);

// ✅ 
const computedValue = useMemo(() => expensiveCalc(data), [data]);

// ❌ Giant components (>200 lines with business logic)
// ❌ Props drilling more than 2 levels → use Zustand or composition
// ❌ Direct Zustand store mutation in JSX event handlers — use action functions
```

## Accessibility Basics

- Interactive elements must have accessible labels
- Use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`)
- Focus management for step navigation
- Color contrast ratio minimum 4.5:1
